bug.short_desc: list of projects should be searchable via suggestions

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1177 illustration of how suggestions could work for Opengrok
With sites with big number of projects (e.g. src.opensolaris.org) it should beneficial for users to be able to search the list projects (ala Firefox search field suggestions) as a way how to select particular project.
For instance to select nightingale project, the user would hit 'n', 'i' letters and this would lock on the project because it is unambiguously determined by the 2 letters (see the attached screenshot).
Obviously there would have to be a new way how to select a project for searching.

this was fixed with latest trunk changes to have project autocomplete using jquery
more convenient stuff is to happen with integration of 11749
hence I am closing this bug
